Week 4 – Data Understanding and GitHub

“In Week 4, we learned how to understand the quality and distribution of data.

Column Quality
This shows the percentage of valid values, empty values, and error values in a column.
It helps us quickly identify whether the data is clean or if there are issues.

Column Distribution
This shows how the values in a column are distributed, including unique values and repeated values.
It helps us understand patterns and frequency of data.

Column Statistics
This provides statistical information about numeric columns, such as:

Minimum value

Maximum value

Average

Standard deviation.

We also discussed KPIs (Key Performance Indicators), which are metrics used to measure performance, such as revenue growth or business performance.

In this week, we also created a GitHub repository and organized our project files into different folders for better project management.”
